    <header>
        <h1><span class="title" itemprop="name" data-bind="text:title">Please, Beards + Design A Wave</span></h1>
    </header>

    <img class="picture pull-right img-responsive" itemprop="image" data-fieldname="picture" src="/media/cache/55/c3/55c3b98863eb12bb833799dd6613a3c0.jpg" width="400" height="400" data-src="/static/img/events/filler.png" data-width="400" data-height="400" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#img-picture-789" alt="" data-bind="attr: { src: pictureData().displaySrc, width: pictureData().displayWidth, height: pictureData().displayHeight, 'data-src': pictureData().src, 'data-width': pictureData().width, 'data-height': pictureData().height }" /><div class="modal " id="img-picture-789">    <div class="modal-dialog">        <div class="modal-content">            <div class="modal-header">                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">                    &times;                </button>            </div>            <div class="modal-body">                <img src="/static/img/events/filler.png" class="img-responsive" alt="" data-bind="attr: {src: pictureData().displaySrc}">            </div>        </div>    </div></div>

    

    <h3><time class="startDateTime" itemprop="startDate" datetime="2011-03-19 20:00:00+00:00" data-bind="attr:{datetime:startDateTime()},text:displayStart()">8:00 p.m. Saturday 19</time> to <time class="endDateTime" itemprop="endDate" datetime="2011-03-20 00:00:00+00:00" data-bind="attr:{datetime:endDateTime()},text:displayEnd()">12:00 a.m. Sunday 20 March 2011</time></h3>

    <meta itemprop="image" content="/media/cache/55/c3/55c3b98863eb12bb833799dd6613a3c0.jpg">

    <div class="bodysection">
        <div class="body" itemprop="about" data-fieldname="body" data-bind="htmlValue:body"><p>A Glimpse Of Paradise + the Star And Shadow Cinema present:</p>
<p><span class="text_exposed_show"><img height="506" src="/static/img/import/5509112675_d60b7b2dc6_z.jpg?origsrc=http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5295/5509112675_d60b7b2dc6_z.jpg" width="640" /></span><strong>PLEASE</strong> ( UPSET THE RHYTHM / LONDON )</p>
<p><em>Prog  punk, Psychedelic Surf-sludge and Middle Eastern Romper Stompers that  will have you blissed off your chonk! Call it what you like or define  them how you will, <strong>PLEASE</strong> are quite simply one of the most fun and  enjoyable live bands making</em><span class="text_exposed_show"><em> waves in the UK right now.With  an excellent 10" already under their belts on <strong>OUSE RECORDS </strong>and an even  tastier long player in the piepline on <strong>UPSET THE RHYTHM</strong>, <strong>PLEASE </strong>are a  band who have gone from strength to strength Karate Kid style, having  wowed and powed audiences across the UK and Europe now for the best part  of 4 years.Musically, <strong>PLEASE</strong> clean out the stable of 60s and  70s Psych-Garage, Prog Jangle and OUT THERE rock; sweeping it all up  into fresh, gratifying song chunks full of clattering Drums, duelling  Guitars and brazen, bravado vocal stylings that are enough to get  anyone's pulse soaring.If you haven't yet succumbed to the  charms of PLEASE, then what better night to do so than on a sunny  Saturday in March at the <strong>STAR AND SHADOW</strong> in Newcastle!</em><strong>Recommended cuts: 'CLOTHES' / 'THE SHAME'</strong><a href="http://www.ouse.org.uk/bands.html"><span>http://www.ouse.org.uk/ban</span>ds.html</a><a href="http://www.myspace.com/pleees"><span>http://www.myspace.com/ple</span>ees</a></span></p>
<p><span class="text_exposed_show"><a href="http://www.myspace.com/pleees"></a><strong>BEARDS</strong> ( OUSE RECORDS / LEEDS )</span></p>
<p><span class="text_exposed_show"><em>At  first, <strong>BEARDS</strong>’ sound might point to freethinking post punks such as  Delta 5 or The Minutemen, but given a double take - the almost all  female trio (!) cunningly blend Punk-Disco with Progressive time  signatures, moments of majestic AOR, Beefheart esque stomps and Post  Hardcore angles, waylaying any ideas of 'Progness' or 'Punkness' along  the way</em>.In short: FANTASTIC PARTY FUNDER LIKE A BOLT TO YOUR BRAIN!<strong>Recommended cut: 'SPINNING COIN'</strong><a href="http://ouse.org.uk/bands.html"><span>http://ouse.org.uk/bands.h</span>tml</a><a href="http://www.myspace.com/beards2000"><span>http://www.myspace.com/bea</span>rds2000</a></span></p>
<p><span class="text_exposed_show"><strong>DESIGN A WAVE</strong> ( ALTER RECORDS / LONDON )</span></p>
<p><span class="text_exposed_show"><em><strong>DESIGN A WAVE</strong> (Or 'DES WAVE' to his pals)</em></span><span class="text_exposed_show"><em> is the Skewed and dishelved/other worldy Funk sound of CLECKHUDDERSFAX's Tom Hirst. Named  after a street gang in the TROMA film 'SURF NAZIS MUST DIE', <strong>DESIGN A  WAVE</strong> serves up a pleasingly dreamy mix of Melancholic Synth Pop, Italo  Disco Juicy-ness and icey cool Cold Wave sounds shone through white  diamond pop nuggets hand picked from a Tropical Island on the Moon.</em><strong>Recommended cut: 'REMEDY'</strong><a href="http://soundcloud.com/deswav"><span>http://soundcloud.com/desw</span>av</a><a href="http://www.designawave.co.uk/"><span>http://www.designawave.co.</span>uk/</a></span></p>
<p><span class="text_exposed_show"><strong>WHENZ ALL THIS HAPPENING THEN???</strong></span></p>
<p><span class="text_exposed_show">SATURDAY  19TH MARCH at the STAR AND SHADOW CINEMA, NEWCASTLE. Tickets cost just  £5 and are available to buy online from wegotickets.com. The party  starts at 8pm with DJs and Disco 'til late and is SURE TO BE A BOBBY  BELTA! Don't miss it.<a href="http://www.wegottickets.com/event/112240"><span>http://www.wegottickets.co</span>m/event/112240</a>Hop on to the A GLIMPSE OF PARADISE Facemince and Blog page for updates on forthcoming shindigs and shows<a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/A-Glimpse-Of-Paradise/191636804186106"><span>http://www.facebook.com/pa</span><span>ges/A-Glimpse-Of-Paradise/</span>191636804186106</a><a href="http://aglimpseofparadise.blogspot.com/"><span>http://aglimpseofparadise.</span>blogspot.com/</a></span></p>
<p><span class="text_exposed_show">x</span></p></div>
    </div>

